    "created_at": "2015-07-17T04:40:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-17T05:03:20Z",
    "body": "I just ran into this using [remark](https://github.com/gnab/remark), a browser-based slideshow tool. It [tries to detect the presence of `window.opener`](https://github.com/gnab/remark/blob/e034c9f0d541124cc54152f34d036e4c25ffc124/src/remark/models/slideshow/navigation.js#L94-L96) before calling it.\n\nIt seems like the current behavior of raising an error is not ideal. I would expect `window.opener` to either be `null`, or to silently noop, or even to be an alternate way of calling `ipc.send`.\n"
